{{wikipedia|Abortion}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''abortio'', from ''aboriri''; see also [[abort]].

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)ʃən|-ɔː(r)ʃən]]

===Noun===
'''abortion''' (''plural'' '''abortions''')

#*<!--DefA-->The [[cessation]] of [[pregnancy]] or fetal development; a [[miscarriage]].
#* An [[induced abortion]].
#<!--DefB--> The act of inducing abortion.
#<!--DefC--> The [[immature]] product of an [[untimely]] birth.
#<!--DefD--> {{biology}} Arrest of development of any organ, so that it remains an [[imperfect]] formation or is [[absorbed]].
#<!--DefE--> Any fruit or produce that does not come to [[maturity]], or anything which in its progress, before it is [[matured]] or perfect
#<!--DefF--> A complete failure.
#:''His attempt proved an '''abortion'''.''
#<!--DefG-->The act of aborting a project, a mission, etc, before it is completed.
#{{Art}} Something ugly, an artistic atrocity.
#:'''1846''' ''Insomuch that I do honestly believe, there can be no place in the world, where such intolerable '''abortions''', begotten of the sculptor's chisel, are to be found in such profusion, as in Rome.'' — Charles Dickens, ''Pictures from Italy'', [http://etext.virginia.edu/etcbin/ot2www-pubeng?specfile=/texts/english/modeng/publicsearch/modengpub.o2w&act=text&offset=269656481&textreg=2&query=abortion&id=DicPict Chapter 10.].


